ules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:714:\"<p>Let&#8217;s assume you&#8217;re working with code along these lines:</p>\n<pre class=\"brush: php; title: ; notranslate\">\r\n$events = tribe_get_events();\r\nforeach ($events as $event):\r\n\r\n    // ... Code to print out event details ...\r\n\r\nendforeach;\r\n</pre>\n<p>You may wish to ignore multiday events, however. In that case, you can use the <em>tribe_is_multiday()</em> function wrapped around your query results. For example:</p>\n<pre class=\"brush: php; title: ; notranslate\">\r\n$events = tribe_get_events();\r\nforeach ($events as $event):\r\n    if (! tribe_event_is_multiday()):\r\n\r\n        // ... Code to print out event details ...\r\n\r\n    endif;\r\nendforeach;\r\n</pre>\n<p>That should get you where you need to be.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"http://tri.be/querying-ongoing-and-single-day-events-separately/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:56:\"Altering or Removing Headings on Calendar and List Views\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:38:\"http://tri.be/alter-or-remove-heading/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_b